Tami selvan																	Git - Getting started
																	
- Version Control System - VCS 
-  Software designed to record changes made to files over time
-  ability to reverth the previous changes 
-


Three stages of the file 
		- commited 
		- modified
		- staged 

Three stages of a git project
		- working directory 
		- staging area [index]
		- .get directory [repository]
		

- man git - gives the manual for git 

- git help config - gives only the config file manual 
- git help - shorter commanly used commands 

- each project in the git are referenced as the repository in the git
- git init - this commands initialize the empty git repository
- .git folder contains all the metadata about the project
- Code hosting providers - github , bitbucket etc

1. git add 
2. git commit -m "first commit "
3. git remote origin https://github.com/TamilTintin/Git-file.git
4. git push -u origin  master 

- git status - to get the status of the current branch and commit 

- git diff --staged - to get the difference  - learn this one more in detail 

- git commit -a -m "Message" - skip the add command 

- git log - history of commit  , git log --oneline 

- check the chris beams blog about the commit messages  - https://chris.beams.io/posts/git-commit/

- git rm file name - to remove the file 

- git rm --cached filename - this command will not delete the file , but it will not track the file 

- git mv oldfilename newfilename - to rename a file 

-  https://git-school.github.io/visualizing-git/

- git checkout -n branchname 

- branch - a light weight pointer 

- git stash ? 

- git reset -  three options - soft, mixed , hard













